	<td bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	<td class="subjectbar" height="20" style="font-size: 8pt;padding-left:10px;" width="100%">
		Re: Discuss Class Re-Envisionment

	</td>
	
		<td class="subjectbar" align=right style="padding:0px;padding-right:10px;">












		<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 id="io_bwizardbalancem2540_table" 
		
			onClick="setId('2540');showLiMenu(this,'io_bwizardbalancem2540','right',false);" 
			onDblClick="setId('2540');showLiMenu(this,'io_bwizardbalancem2540','right',false);" 
			
		>
		<tr class=clickable>
			
				<td nowrap><a class=subjectbar_text style='font-size: 8pt;'>Options</a></td>
				
			<td>&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>
			<td><img src='/i/skins/default/button_options.gif' border=0 alt='Options' title='Options' width=11 height=28></td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
		</table>
		
		</td></tr>
		
	<tr>
	
		<td class="msg_user_cell" width="150" valign=top>
		
			 









<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=95852'  class="auth_text"  style="font-weight:bold;" >	
Khaine_Darkaster</a>
			<br>
			
			<span style="font-size: 8pt;">
			Newbie<br>
			
				Posts: 4<br>
				
				Registered: 03-15-2005
				
			</span>
			


			
			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=95852'>







</a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=wizardbalance&message.id=2540#M2540">51</a> of 234
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 497 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			Hi, ignore the british sense of humour. This is a positive post!<br><br>The proposed manaburn changes are welcome, very much so. The changes made to cope with misuse of it on old Kunark mobs were heavy handed, and largely made it a pointless item. I agree with others that the changes to it must be careful. Nobody wants a repeat of manaburn teams patrolling Norrath like a deranged arcane hit-squad. On the other hand, it would be nice to use it occasionally, instead of regretting the loss of the AA's spent on it. <br><br><br>Rains have been a little used line, which should become viable and fun to use with the changes to resist rate. I always liked the idea, and they were a nice alternate option to the "One Nuke Wizard" syndrome which saw a potentially tactical class sitting there pounding a single nuke button, going oom and then watching the tanks do the real work.<br><br>Removing the Plus mana cap. I have nothing but positive things to say about that. When it was implemented, wizards took the brunt of the negative effects it induced.<br><br>The new line of dps spells. It's a great idea! I love it as a concept. Is it high enough in DPS? I'm not sure. If put in context of against tanks? Melee do better dps with no restriction on how long they last. (Other than the healers, which also guard our frail potential corpses). <br>We expend a manabar, they just plug on regardless. In that context, the line appears too low in DPS. We could throw in a big nuke to up it, but we are still spending a finite resource to try to compete with classes which do not, and losing.<br>The idea of mana, surely, was supposed to restrict us being more powerful. Well, we are not more powerful. With the manabar, we are less powerful, AND we are on a timer. I'm not suggesting the manabar go, heavens no. But this does need looking at. The problem is of course that it is a far ranging subject, with many ramifications. I'm not blind to that, and I know there is no easy fix. I would be horrified to see one. I bow to the number crunchers on this, of which there are far too many for my ego to cope with. <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0><br><br>The extended problem is, Sony has focused on grouping, yet the wizard has not been a grouping character for some time. We nuke, and we provide the taxi home at the end of the night. That's it as far as our functionality and scope go. While we did impressive damage, we were happy with that. It's what we signed on for at Wizard School.<br>The problem came when we started getting serious competition by classes which could do nearly as well as us in our chosen area, and so very much more in others.<br>Sony has given the impression in the past that they were not entirely sure what to do with the wizard. Any additions to the class meant we stepped on the toes of others, yet our toes are flat as pancakes. (flat pancakes, obviously).<br><br><br>That being said, the proposed changes are BOLD, and as a player who started pre-kunark, I havn't seen much of that in the past. It's refreshing, and it's promising! I can see some very original thought has gone into some of the proposals, and that can only be a good thing. Well done from an old Dark Elf.<br><br><br>One last thing however, (Columbo impression).<br>Al'Kabor. I don't hate the man personally. His spell line however: The functionality of this spell line, is either the greatest kept secret at Sony, (Wizards sure don't get it), or the spell line is simply no good. <br>Wizards once said that about AE spells in general, before some bright spark came up with the AE group, but Al'Kabor.....what have you done you silly wizard. <br>Currently, the spell line performs one use. That is to increase points in research when trying to make it. I know of no sane wizard who uses this spell line for long after he gains his first example of it.<br><br>It offers the chance to replace it with something original, and useful. Go nuts. We won't miss it, and we will stop heckling the man himself when he occasionally shows up. Well, a little good natured ribbing might still be owed for some years into the future, but other than that....<br><br><br>Thanks for reading, assuming you did. Keep up the good work. The changes are Hill Giant's step in the right direction.<br><br><br><br>Khaine	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
