		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>Another issue that I just thought about on the MB issue is that our nukes have become somewhat more efficient from what they were at the Luclin era. Garrison's Superior Sunder was 3.89 damage per nuke, and Manaburn was (iirc) 2.00 damage per mana. Now, in OoW we're sitting at Ancient: Core Fire at 4.79, so if the MB was to scale proportionally it would have to be 2*4.79/3.89 ~ 2.46 damage per mana. You could argue that this won't really be a problem, because you'll hit the %-hp cap on the mob so any excess is wasted, but I will say that it might change the way in which MB is used, to be burned only when you're down to 50 mana, in which case this extra efficiency would have an impact.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>As far as my personal opinion goes, this MB fix is just something put in to shut up the whining minority of wizards that want MB restored to it's former glory. To those I say, give it up, it's not gonna happen.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I would rather ask for the offensive/conserving/subtle stances that have been described above, or maybe even ask for Frenzied Devastation/Prolonged Devastation to just be made into a CoCo ability instead (Click on, Click off) - that way we can increase our DPS by roughly 33% while increasing our manausage by 100% (if you use that on the 4.79 Ancient:Core Fire above, you get 3.11 efficiency instead of 4.79, but 33% more DPS at the same aggro level as we had before).</DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
