		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>Taking a look at the wizard top 10 list, I think it needs a re-vamp in itself.&nbsp; Manaburn #1 ?&nbsp; Who cares, though we all love the big boom is it really the most important factor?&nbsp; Even if it did 50k everytime it still is relatively pointless due to recast and the strain on mana.&nbsp; Pre-nerf or not, it was, i, and always will be nothing but a toy.&nbsp; No reason to keep it as number one.&nbsp; Pillar spells are number 2.&nbsp; We all want groups, so why put a solo activity as a high priority?&nbsp; Seems a bit contradictory imo.&nbsp; Rain spells are and pretty much always have been useless, even without resists they are typically less dps than single target spells.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I think there are some great ideas in here....I especially liked the 1st post by Ammelen.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Burst DPS</DIV>
<DIV>Sustained DPS </DIV>
<DIV>Aggro Management</DIV>
<DIV>Resist Rate</DIV>
<DIV>Groupability</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>These seem to be the hot topics currently, maybe have Ashlanne do some updating?&nbsp; No reason to have in pointless items that do not pertain to the basis of the class itself.&nbsp; There are many petty things to ask for like no TL fragments, which are logical.&nbsp; However, keeping the focus on specific and essential issues seems more relevant.&nbsp; I would use emeralds for porting if I could keep up with a warrior in sustained dps and out parse a rogue on Arch Magnus.&nbsp; For the first time in a long while it seems there is a genuine look at the classes, would be nice to have our ducks in a row and worry about the true issues instead of pointless crap like manaburn.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>**Great job pushing with Manaburn Manifesto and such, and I agree with it completely!&nbsp; Would just rather see that kind of push for something more practical for the class.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>	
