			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>im just gonna post what i did on Graffes, youll ahve to pardon me i was a bit peeved when i typed them, but the gist is the same, and the concepts dont change....</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>first post was</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Wanna fix mana burn, bloody &nbsp;make it do 1 to 1.25 or even 1.5 damage per mana in your POOL, remove that&nbsp; one MB per 3 minute crap, AND make it so you loose NO mana when its used.<BR><BR>what would this cause that is SOOOOOO bloody imbalanced? if anything? WOOOOOHOOOOOOO i could nuke for 10k every 2 hours one time for free,&nbsp; i can do that several times with a little mana and popping Frenzied Devistation. (speeking of which, im suddenly critting with this at way less than 50% did it get changed?)<BR><BR><BR>HOWEVER this WOULD make manaburn usefull to all levels of players, it would scale with the mana pool (IE gear) and would even help a tad with both Burst DPS and slightly longer raid fights as well.<BR><BR>As for Rains, yeah it looks nice, but they should really look into focus effects for rains, a is they are situational due to mez and CC. And really, if they are STILL worried about this getting used for soloing, maybe they should play the class and see how much EXP that gets you compared to grouping in a good zone.<BR><BR>Im not meaning to bitch, but id rather not see poeple get so happy we FINALY get thrown a bone that SoE thinks they have done enough. When i watch a Shammies buff proc almost 1 time per second (he buffed several pets) and each of those procs is 450 damage.... Thats 450DPS PLUS his DoTs, plus every other utility this class has....<BR><BR>As far as im concerned SoE had better come up with ALOT more to fix the issues in EQ, they have run a TYPICAL "Monty Hall Campaign" and the current imbalances are due to that. Any good DM whos played a P&amp;P RPG could spot this a mile away, but SoE cant seem to grasp it even though it kicks them in the but EVERY expansion.<BR><BR><BR>sorry for the rant-ish part of that, been a LOOOOOOOONG time coming, hehe i do feel a hair better though </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>second post was</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV>see thats just it, manaburn COULD BE good for burst DPS every couple hours, what i described is in NO way imbalancing.<BR><BR>As for rains that pretty much what i was saying, they are very situational, but should be ALOT better in those situations, as is if they lift the 20% resist mod, they will only be slightly better.<BR><BR>As for Claw of Vox.... well first problem, i did not play a wizard so i could crit for about 3500 tops on average. Second whats teh absolute BEST DPS you could get with that spell anyhow? 300? Maybe a hair more? Mellees that are NOT DPS are reaching well beyond that now, and while i agree rogues should do more damage over long periods, we SHOULD be no less than 3rd or 4rth on the list of top damage in long duration. DAMAGE IS WHAT WE DO.<BR><BR>To make matters worse, im nto sure how i see Claw of Vox being infinitely sustainable really. 208 mana per cast, which means the average caster even WITH all the AAs maxxed that can possably get you FT gains about what, 75 mana a tic sitting. Now ill be nice and say that with a 10% mana pres item, and SCM maxxed will spend about 140 or so ave on a cast that is still more mana than they regain in a constant pull scenario. Fact is we are STILL left unable to do even 300DPS in a constant pull scenario.<BR><BR>To be quite honest the only way i see them being able to bring wizards up on long term DPS without over powering us is through indirect damage, be it really good damage shields, the ability to make others proc minor wiz spells or some such, whatever. As for short term DPS, a REAL mana burn fix, FD NOT taking double mana and fixxing the bloody resist rates would go a LOOOOONG way.<BR><BR>One of the things SoE used to say wizards had as an advantage was the ability to use all forms of elemental magic, fire, ice, and magic based nukes.... well fire is going well, magic is going well, **SMURF** is up with Ice... not only do our ice nukes SUCK compared to the others, but finding anything better than a 20% standard focus for it is an absolute PITA for anyone not doing Velkitorin or better. This sucks considering Magic Foci can be picked up from LDON, DON, WoS random drops and about 1,000,000 other places, and Fire can be picked up from VP quest, DoN, or Nobles Causeway (well for wizards, mages have that ring).</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>if others dont agree thats fine, but those are my opinions as i stated them there.</DIV></DIV>	
