		" 
			>
			<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Giants56 wrote:<BR>
<DIV></DIV><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>

<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>All spells will check for immunity before they are cast.&nbsp; So if the target is immune, the spell will not generate aggro for the caster.</DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>This made me think about concussion and ancient greater concussion.</P>
<P>From reading Graffe's and from personal experience, i have always believed that the&nbsp;aggro reduction&nbsp;effect works when the spell is cast even if the text states: "Your target resisted the ancient greater concussion spell". If this isn't the case, the concussion spell would be extremely ineffective given the frequency of the resist messages. </P>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV>Resist != immune</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Conc works when resisted.&nbsp; I do not know of any mobs that are i<STRONG>mmune </STRONG>to concussion, although I think there are a few mobs which are completely immune to magic.</DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=322309">Ambrielle Aphaedra</a> &ltHeroes of Kaladim&gt<br><br>I(90%) N(90%) T(71%) P(87%)<br><br>"The real threat to the life of the nation .... comes not from terrorism but from laws such as these [Terrorism Act]" - Lord Hoffman (16 Dec 2004) finding against the UK governement on the matter of detention without trial.
