		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<blockquote><hr>EC_Ruggers wrote:<br><DIV>SoWizard sustained dps hasalready been balanced with DoN via claw of vox ...and nowyou will limpliment it for all the lowbie wizards. Wow I feel loved. Good thing there is not many wizards left to complain about this. Oh and now that the mana buff cap effects other classes we will fix it. Wizards have only been asking for this since pop came out. All in all I think you droped the ball on this sony. We need a larger overhaul then claw of vox and its sub 200 dps. AndI will belive a mana burn fix when I see it. </DIV><br><hr></blockquote><br>No, we aren't necessarily "balanced" by Claw of Vox.  The goal of the current game changes is to address gameplay issues, not performance issues.  Charm is essentially a dead gameplay mechanic so they're going to revive it.  Same with fear.  All the patch message meant in regard to wizard and Claw of Vox was that in group situations that require sustained damage, wizards have <em>something</em>.  Later on, they will evaluate whether or not that something is <em>enough</em>.
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
