	<tr>
	
		<td class="msg_user_cell" width="150" valign=top>
		
			 









<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=95709'  class="auth_text"  style="font-weight:bold;" >	
<span style='color:#3399FF;font-weight:bold; '>Ammelen</span></a>
			<br>
			
			<span style="font-size: 8pt;">
			Champion<br>
			
				Posts: 316<br>
				
				Registered: 03-14-2005
				
			</span>
			


			
			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=95709'>







</a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=wizardbalance&message.id=2558#M2558">65</a> of 234
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 406 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			I agree with the above poster who said we need to not focus too much on manaburn.  It's just one aa skill and is not class defining in any way.  One 10k or even 20k nuke ever 2.5 hours has a minimal effect on sustained dps.  When you consider the loss of mana required for it, it lowers sustained dps.  It also lowers burst dps in almost any circumstance because it takes all your mana and is nowhere near as efficient as your big nukes.  Yes, I'd like to see it unnerfed, I think we all would.  But whether or not they do anything with manaburn is not going to change the basic problems of the class, which are dramatically sub par sustained damage and unimpressive burst damage.  That is what needs to be fixed to make the wizard class desirable.  No one is going to want us in a group because we can do 1 20k nuke per 2.5 hours followed by 10 minutes of sitting on our ass doing no damage.  The LAST THING we want right now is to get throne some manaburn toy in the place of a real class fixing.<br><br>As the last poster mentioned, the current claw line is woefully inadequate in increasing sustained damage for 2 reasons.  First, the MAX sustainable damage with it, assuming we get every nuke off and have no mana issues and there are no resists, is insufficient.  Claw of Vox does 1375 damage.  So let's assume that you have 45% cold focus to 70 (not even sure if this is in the game yet, maybe will be on anguish legs soon).  That makes the average increased damage 23%, so your damage is 1691.25.  The cast time of the nuke is 5.0s.  Take off 10% for the AA, 10% for cleric spell haste, 23% for quickening of druzzil, and you are left with 2.85s.  Recycle time on spell bar is 2.25s, so you can nuke once per 5.1s.  This gives a maximum possible sustained damage, if there are zero resists, of 1691.25/5.1= ***** 331.6 DPS *****.<br><br>Do you have any idea how bad 331.6 DPS is for an anguish geared (with those foci) level 70 dps class with 1200 AA?  This is the ABSOLUTE ideal with the claw line, something few wizards could reach.  And on top of it, the mana cost for Claw of Vox makes it IMPOSSIBLE to sustain this dps.  We would be oom, even with max aa's, gear, foci, enchanter, bst, and and bard in group.<br><br>Let's now consider the average grouping situation, where we would have a mana regen of 2 base (we can't sit since we must chain cast with the vox line), 20 for FT (assuming all expansive mind AA's), 20 for Voice of Clairvoyance.  That gives a mana regen of 42 mana/tick.  Familiar adds 8, so we're at 50/tick.  Assume we're uber and have Maelin's Methodical Mind or some other brain clicky.  Now we're at 58 mana/tick.  Now, let's throw a bard in group, that's another 20 or so per tick (not sure exactly, but that's about right), so we're up to 78 mana/tick.  Claw of Vox costs 208 mana to cast.  With specialization, we might take off 20% (not sure on this number, if anyone has better, pls let me know) and 20% mana preservation focus to 70 (very rare) would average 10.5% preservation, so we're at 31.5% preservation, giving us a final mana cost of 142.5 mana per cast.  We regen 78 mana/tick, so that's 78/6=13 mana per second.  That is 142.5/13=10.96s per cast that can be sustained, meaning we can cast once per 11s and sustain it indefinitely.  Once per 11s gives us a dps of 1691.25/11= ***** 153.75 DPS *****.  Some zones are outdoors, so you could use a mount, that would increase mana regen to about 99/tick.  This gives a total dps number, by the above methodology, of ***** 195 DPS *****.  And how often are we sitting in a group with a bard and enchanter both there where we can use our mounts, where we have every uber focus in the game, and where we have ZERO resists?  Umm, like never.  But 195 DPS is the upper ceiling on sustained dps for us with the claw line at its current mana cost.<br><br>195 dps with zero resists, 100% hit rate!  This is UNACCEPTABLE.  My warrior friends do about 400-450 dps in group.  My rogue friends do 750-800 dps.  That puts a warrior at more than 2x a wizard's sustained dps with claw and a rogue at about 4x us.  That is our IDEAL, max possible dps too, compared to their average, realized dps.  SK's and Paladins exceed this number by a large margin.  ONE QUARTER OF A ROGUE, IF EVERYTHING IS PERFECT?  That's not a fix.  That is not an answer.<br><br>This shows just how screwed up wizards are as a class.  Our sustained dps is not even in the ballpark of what it needs to be.  We don't need 10 or even 50% increases in dps.  We need 300% increases in sustained dps.<br><br>Let's take a look at burst dps too.  Assume that for burst we will use Ancient: Core Fire.  Now, not all wizards have this, but this is what I would use, and we are examining the high end.  Use 45% focus again, which averages 23% increase in dps.  That would give us 4070 * .23 = 5006.1 damage.  Casst time is 8.0s, with 10% for cleric haste, 10% for nuke AA, and 23% spell haste, we're at 4.6s.  This is better than most of my guild's wizards have, but it's the best possible circumstance.  With recast time, that's 6.85s between nukes.  That gives us a burst dps, as long as we have mana, of 5006.1/6.85s=730.82 DPS.  Now, this isn't as horrible as the sustained numbers, not by a long shot.  Throw in the AA and we're probably up around a thousand dps.  However, my rogue friends SUSTAIN more than 730 DPS (not a lot more, but a bit more) in a regular XP group without anything special.  When a rogue discs, he's doing over 2k DPS.  We need to up our burst dps for regular circumstances to about 1k DPS, and with a long reuse AA like frenzied to the 2k-3k range (for a short time,and at high mana cost).<br><br>Please look at these numbers SOE and let me know what you think.	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
