			No way is manaburn class defining.  Can you think of another class defining ability that doesn't even exist in the game without lvl 60 and multiple AA's?  I know level 70 wizards in uberguilds that don't even have manaburn, and do their jobs just fine.  I myself have it, and cast it maybe once per 2 months, and I play every day.  It's a toy, definitely not a class defining ability, and will do little or nothing towards fixing the major problems with the wizard class.  While we'd like it unnerfed, and I agree it should not be capped as it is and should be affected by foci, this is a VERY minor thing compared to our issues with pathetic sustained dps.<br><br>What would you rather have, the ability to do a rogue's dps in group (4x your current sustained dps) or the ability to land a 20k nuke ever 2.5 hours, decreasing your total sustained dps?<br><br>Which do you think would make you more groupable or useful on raids?<br><br>Manaburn is a toy and nothing more.	
		</td></tr>
