<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=wizardbalance&message.id=2564#M2564">71</a> of 234
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 367 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>Let me preface this post with my earlier computations and what my assumptions are:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>SCM3 = 10% mana reduction</DIV>
<DIV>Spec:Evoc(200) = 10% mana reduction</DIV>
<DIV>All critical AA (wiz) = 22% critical rate</DIV>
<DIV>Destructive Fury AA = 25% extra critical damage</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Focus used</DIV>
<DIV>50% Cold Damage (Worn)</DIV>
<DIV>25% E'ci Familiar (Spell)</DIV>
<DIV>20% Manapreservation Focus</DIV>
<DIV>23% Spell Haste Focus</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Claw of Vox, 1375 dd, 208&nbsp;mp, 5s cast</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Without Fizzles and Resists at <STRONG>all</STRONG>:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Focused Damage: 1375*(1+1*(22%*125%+50%/2+25%/2)) = 2268 damage on average</DIV>
<DIV>Focused Mana: 208*(1-10%-10%-20%/2)&nbsp;= 146 mana on average</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>This is an average efficiency of 15.5 damage per mana expended, for every mana/tick regen that the wizard can regenerate this would translate into roughly 15/6 = 2.5 damage per second.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The basic problem with balancing wizards, is the conversion factor of raw mana-regen per tick into damage. It's at the very high end now, and that makes wizards very highly "geared" in the sense that an input of, say, 10 mana/tick regen translates into a 25 sustained dps upgrade (folllowing the 15 damage per mana, 150 damage per tick). Adding some classes to the group does alot for wizards, just based on their mana regen capabilities:<BR><BR>WIZ, 49/tick base, 122.5 dps (50% medding, FS click, Focus Flappy, MC3, HoD/Harvests (8), FT20)<BR>DRU, +9/tick, +22.5dps<BR>BST, +10/tick, +25dps + perfection which is 660 mana every xx minutes<BR>BRD, +22/tick, +55dps + focus<BR>ENC, +20/tick, +50dps<BR>NEC, +30/tick, +75dps<BR><BR>That's 370 dps, sustained (530 dps "per mob" in a 70% uptime group) - but isn't happening <B>ever</B> in an exp group, <STRONG>but how do you balance a class that has such a high volatility and is so dependent on other classes buffs</STRONG>?<BR><BR>Well, my suggestion that's more than a year old now was to give wizards self-buffs, one for each "foreign" that gave a bit less regen than the "foreign" buff itself, this to alleviate the <B>extreme</B> dependency on "foreign" buffs to perform&nbsp;well in groups.<!-- / message --></DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=370955 target=_blank> Aauminki Troldmand</a><br><a href=http://cc.alderaan.nu/>Caer Cadarn</a> (Euro Raiding Guild)<br>Maelin Starpyre Server
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
