			Gnomish Greetings!<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Noinim wrote:<BR>
<DIV>In my mind's eye, I have always thought Wizards were to be the best at burst DPS. It wasn't the sustained DPS that made us enticing, it was the kaboom factor, our quick killing ability when needed. I always thought our burst DPS was more important than our sustained. This is only the way I seen it. I know almost no one will agree to that. I just want to see big nukes, in a fast time. I want to be able to annhilate[sp?] anything in an instant. That was our place, so I thought.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>As far as manaburn, the way i read it, we get the unnerfed form back as so much as it does not take out more than a certain % of mob life. Just like how they cut it back for PvP originally, where u could manaburn for i thinnk 70% of it's life. Now honestly, if you cant make it there, it lands to full just like it did before (i think some did crits into 20k+ area) so long as it did not account for more than a certain % (which will be announced later) of a mob's life.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>My thoughts/suggestions:</DIV>
<DIV>Give us that ungodly burst factor back. I would take a decent sustained (even if it was behind certain classes) if I was holy hell capable of blowing something to bits. I'm talkin' 1k burst DPS or more. I want it dead, two years ago.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>If manaburn is back to it's old form as I think, I hope it scales better now that we have those high end mana pools (sorry I just hit the 5k mark, but i am trying to work on it). It should rock just as good for those 10k manapools as it did in Luclin for the 4500-5000 manapools.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>My 2 cents.</DIV><BR>
