<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=wizardbalance&message.id=2568#M2568">74</a> of 234
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 336 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			I think most agree that the one area we should be dominant in is burst damage.  What I also believe though is that we should be superior to non dps classes (such as warrior, sk, paladin, etc.) in sustained dps.  We should be on a par with rangers for sustained dps, behind rogues by 20-25%.  We should be superior to all classes in burst dps.<br><br>Burst dps does not mean one nuke though.  Burst dps means how much dps can we do in a 30s or 1min or even 2-5 min period, and manaburn is not the answer to that.  Our "burst dps" is what we do using our big nukes, Ancient: Core Fire or Corona Flare now.  Manaburn doing like 20k even would not give us good burst dps, as it drains all our mana, and we could equal that 20k with 3-4 big nukes.<br><br>What we really want as a class at the high end is good sustained dps on a par with most melee dps classes except rogue.  We also want the best dps of any class in short fights up to several minutes.<br><br>By all means, unnerf manaburn, but not instead of this more important stuff.	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
